title: Letting It Go
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2CyDIC0

by Anonymous

Toni whines as she strains into the bonds. Part of her is desperate to come.The other part of her wants to hold off, not wanting to lose control. Actually all of her is desperate for release - of one form or another - it just happens to be embarrassing when it happens. It shouldn’t feel so good. It should feel dirty and wrong. But it doesn’t. It’s feels so damn good.

title: Iron Fist
body:
So, almost binge watched new season and man, must I say I’m dissapointed. I think that guys at Marvel’ Netflix just don’t like Iron Fist story and don’t know what to do with it.

What with Netflix and superpowers being a synonim for drugs? Now IF is a bad thing that’s corrupts soul, wow. Different colours for different people. It kinda makes sense, but still stupid. And don’t even start on that epiloge thing with charging your weapon with IF energy, it’s destroy the purpose of the thing. Not even asking why Danny has it. Wow, I just thought, it looks like KHR! with theirs Flame’ charged weapons, lol. A sword, a two pistols, different colours for personality type…

Plot is okay. Progressing straight, not leaving big plot lines behind. But. I don’t like that development. Danny being unworthy of his powers, Danny being weaker than before, Danny needing teaching in mind discipline and hand-combat from Colleen, who is swordman and just recently recovered from beinf Handbrainwashed. Right. Danny being not anything like he was in LC. 

From plot point I don’t get why Joy cooperated with Davos. Seriouosly. She helped him and literally next episode turned around and tried to unmade this. And I felt like this ritual of stealing power of IF was a disgrace and some dark stuff, but our heroes just did all that too. Felt wrong.

I loved new plotline that isn’t being connected to the fucking Hand. The Triads are more interesting (through still useless) and close to earth. Don’t like the idea of connection between Colleen family and IF legacy.

The best and only best characters in this seasons are Mary and BB. All other suck. Seriously. 

Maybe in other post some other day I’ll talk about them, but now it looks too big. 

So season is easy to watch, it’s dynamic, but it’s not raising any moral question nor some debate on who is right. And the finale, man. What even was that shit? Maybe part with Colleen was apropriate, but Danny and Ward - really no.

title: Playlist Number 3
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2Qfp8SH

by Book_Lover93

After having a huge fight with her boyfriends, Steve Rogers and Bucky Barnes, just before they left on a week long mission, Reader is feeling lonely and sorry for everything she said. Even worse, she’s under “house arrest” and can’t leave because she got injured on their last mission, so Steve, as Captain, ordered her to stand down. Feeling like shit and in need of some distractions, Reader decides that listening to music is a good course of action to get her mind off the fact that she can’t apologize for their fight and has to wait until they get back. Little does she know that the mission was cut short…
